make a smoke
Homonym Number:
Word Class: phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:to make a smoke signal


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: also put up (a) smoke
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1952 Dec Hollyford Valley, Davie Gunn (advising tyro trampers) HWO `Make a smoke for the steamer at Greenstone [on Lake Wakatipu].'
